policy and planning invitatives at the national, provincial and local levels, new trends in language use in a variety of social domains, and major events concerning languages in mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau and Taiwan. Now for the first time, these reports are available in English for anyone interested in Chinese languge and linguistics, China's language, education and social policies, as well as everyday language use among the ordinary people in China. The invaluable data contained in these reports provide an essential reference to researchers, professionals, policy makers, and China watchers.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 4aChina. 4aChinesisch. 4aSprachpolitik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aChina.  aChinese Language.  aLanguage Policy and Planning.1 aAini, Lin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBo, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaojuan, Zhou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErhong, Yang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuilin, Yu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaimin, Feng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaofeng, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHongbo, Zhou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHongning, Long, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHui, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJia, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJiali, Qin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJuan, Bai, econtributor.4ctb4https://i